summary: i’ll NEVER ever ever forget the first time i heard new year’s day in taylors living room because i vividly remember when the...
body: i’ll NEVER ever ever forget the first time i heard new year’s day in taylors living room because i vividly remember when the first few piano keys played, the room was in absolute silence and i said ‘Oh. my. God’ ‘OH. MY GODDDD’ so loudly right in front of taylor and then immediately started tearing up and crying and then all she did for the entirety of the song was stare and smile at me and the girls at the front while carefully swaying her body and then afterwards she told me i was ‘so cute’ when i cried during the song and i just… can’t handle it i hate being this annoying but i literally cant handle it god help me it’s all too much i literally have the image in my mind of taylor swift staring into my soul as she mouthed the words “and i will hold on to you” i just CANNOT deal with this level of emotion

summary: So today I found out that my uni friend went to the 1989 concert, which I didn’t know somehow (and we’ve been friends for a few...
body:
So today I found out that my uni friend went to the 1989 concert, which I didn’t know somehow (and we’ve been friends for a few months now), and while she was at the concert she got to touch Taylor’s hand!!! Yeah I was pretty jealous, BUT, the best part of the story was that after touching her hand, instead of screaming about how she got to touch @taylorswift, she then screams out:

“SHE MOISTURISES!!! HER HANDS ARE SO SOFT!! SHE’S MOISTURISED!!!”

And I personally think that’s the greatest reaction ever….
